    {
      "id": "Z4GLE2rOgfnuyggvpEBBv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -4049.3356927976,
      "y": 3610.8805367689506,
      "width": 1009.856791559698,
      "height": 631.7700443027321,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b5k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1681959622,
      "version": 2195,
      "versionNonce": 22619267,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773799654314,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Base operating state design Summary\n\nThe user is operating within the network identity layer with similar capabilities to a chatbot +\naccess to local tool use and Enterprise Common Operating Picture \n\nAgents can:\n  - Think, analyze, summarize, plan, communicate, search, read\n  - Fan out to other agents (A2A), gather information, synthesize\n  - Produce recommendations, drafts, plans — as long as they stay in the conversation\n\n  Agents cannot:\n  - Execute plans (write files, create artifacts, send emails, schedule meetings)\n  - Change state in any system outside the conversation\n  - Create durable artifacts (dashboards, documents, code)\n\n  Access gated by Data classification:\n  - Internal and below — open access\n  - Confidential and above — RBAC controlled, need explicit permission\n\n  In the base operating agents are analysts and communicators, not actors. The harness\nis what grants the right to act.\n",
      "fontSize": 22.973456156462984,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Base operating state design Summary\n\nThe user is operating within the network identity layer with similar capabilities to a chatbot + access to local tool use and Enterprise Common Operating Picture \n\nAgents can:\n  - Think, analyze, summarize, plan, communicate, search, read\n  - Fan out to other agents (A2A), gather information, synthesize\n  - Produce recommendations, drafts, plans — as long as they stay in the conversation\n\n  Agents cannot:\n  - Execute plans (write files, create artifacts, send emails, schedule meetings)\n  - Change state in any system outside the conversation\n  - Create durable artifacts (dashboards, documents, code)\n\n  Access gated by Data classification:\n  - Internal and below — open access\n  - Confidential and above — RBAC controlled, need explicit permission\n\n  In the base operating agents are analysts and communicators, not actors. The harness    is what grants the right to act.\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
