      "text": "Inside the Project",
      "fontSize": 43.74371794274594,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Inside the Project",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "qHFrNZ8NnM1QYyF-pOuNZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1118.9475665461437,
      "y": 3634.991776398975,
      "width": 1233.199313384509,
      "height": 402.03548273810225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6C",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 154666758,
      "version": 5549,
      "versionNonce": 422566915,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "LhQLYUivMffqkmyQJZnG4",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1773796363079,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Planning \n\nThis is one of the key functions that is borrowed from NIMS, and aligns with best practices in current\nagentic workflows, always have a plan before you build, manage your tokens wisely. The purpose of the\nplanning protocol is to structurally enforces these best practices.\n\nThe ultimate output of the Planning phase is the Operational Action Plan, which requires human sign off and\ndescribes in details the objectives, bounded operational period length, acceptance criteria, required access,\nagent assignment, type and structure. It is immutable once finalized unless the User stops the operational\nperiod. \n\nIt also launches a hard audit trail on behaviors.\n\nOAPs can be as long as they need to be for very complex work, or as simple as one line for small work. ",
      "fontSize": 22.973456156462984,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Planning \n\nThis is one of the key functions that is borrowed from NIMS, and aligns with best practices in current agentic workflows, always have a plan before you build, manage your tokens wisely. The purpose of the planning protocol is to structurally enforces these best practices.\n\nThe ultimate output of the Planning phase is the Operational Action Plan, which requires human sign off and describes in details the objectives, bounded operational period length, acceptance criteria, required access, agent assignment, type and structure. It is immutable once finalized unless the User stops the operational period. \n\nIt also launches a hard audit trail on behaviors.\n\nOAPs can be as long as they need to be for very complex work, or as simple as one line for small work. ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
